glosses.gloss: A mountainous region of central Italy on the Adriatic
Abruzzi e Molise was formerly one of the regions of Italy encompassing a total of 16,600 km2 and including Abruzzo, Molise and Circondario di Cittaducale.
Abruzzo is a region of Italy in Southern Italy, with an area of 10,763 square km and a population of 1.2 million.
The formerly combined region of Abruzzo and Molise
A former mountainous region of central Italy that borders the Adriatic Sea; properly Abruzzi e Molise; now separated into Abruzzo and Molise.
